01/10/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The European Commission is widely expected to be very positive in its progress reports on Romania and Bulgaria, according to the Bulgarian Telegraph Agency. On Thursday (30 September), it reported on the consensus in both countries. The annual reports, expected next week, help gauge a country's political and economic readiness to join the union. Bulgaria and Romania hope for entry in 2007. 
Also Thursday, Bulgaria announced plans to open a general consulate in the US city of Chicago. It is home to the largest Bulgarian community abroad, an estimated 50,000 people. (BTA, Bulgarian Radio, Novinite - 30/09/04) 
